  "texts": [
    "Then the sequence of projectors {π(P Sn)} is non-increasing and converges in the strong operator topology to the orthogonal projector p S onto the intersection of the ranges of the π(P Sn), see for example [50,Thm 4.32(a)].",
    "In particular, p S is independent of the particular sequence {S n }, and if S is bounded then p S = π(P S).The following proposition is an adaptation of [11,Proposition 5.2] to Levin-Wen models.Proposition 8.1.",
    "Any anyon representation π: A → H has a vector state ψ for which thereis R ≥ 0 such that ψ(B f) = 1 for all f ∈ F such that B f ∈ A B c R. Proof: Let Λ 1, Λ 2 be two cones such that Λ 1 ∪ Λ 2 = R 2,and such that any B f belongs to A Λ 1 or A Λ 2 (or both).Since π satisfies the superselection criterion, there are unitariesU i: H → H for i = 1, 2 such that π| Λ i = (Ad[U i] • π 1)| Λ i.",
    "It follows that ω 1 (x) = ⟨Ω 1, π 1 (x) Ω 1 ⟩ = ⟨Ω 1, U * i π(x)U i Ω 1 ⟩ for all x ∈ A Λ i.",
    "Define states ω i by ω i (x):= ⟨Ω i, π(x)Ω i ⟩ for x ∈ A, where |Ω i ⟩ = U i |Ω 1 ⟩ ∈ H.The states ω i are vector states of π and satisfy ωi (x) = ω 1 (x) for all x ∈ A Λ i."
